import React from 'react'
import {FaBars} from 'react-icons/fa'
import {
    Nav, 
    NavbarContainer, 
    NavLogo, 
    MobileIcon, 
    NavMenu, 
    NavItem, 
    NavLinks,
    NavBtn,
    NavBtnLink 
} from './NavbarElements';

const Navbar = ({ toggle }) => {
    return (
        <>
            <Nav>
              <NavbarContainer>
                <NavLogo to="/">Juan Of A Kind</NavLogo>
                <MobileIcon onClick={toggle}>
                    <FaBars />
                </MobileIcon>
                <NavMenu>
                    <NavItem>
                        <NavLinks to="home">Home</NavLinks>
                    </NavItem>
                    <NavItem>
                        <NavLinks to="menu">Menu</NavLinks>
                    </NavItem>
                    <NavItem>
                        <NavLinks to="about">About</NavLinks>
                    </NavItem>
                    <NavItem>
                        <NavLinks to="contact">Contact</NavLinks>
                    </NavItem>
                    <NavItem>
                        <NavLinks to="catering">Catering</NavLinks>
                    </NavItem>
                    <NavItem>
                        <NavLinks to="store">Store</NavLinks>
                    </NavItem>
                </NavMenu>
                <NavBtn>
                    <NavBtnLink to="/placeorder">Place Order</NavBtnLink>
                </NavBtn>
              </NavbarContainer>       
            </Nav>
        </>
    )
}

export default Navbar;
